G-MOE-SIMD-TOKS — NORTHSTAR brick 5: SIMD row dot + dequant-free expert rows (2026-07-02)
=========================================================================================
BUILT (submodule):
- q36_dot_i8xf32 (forward_dispatch.c): AVX2+FMA i8*f32 dot (8-lane cvtepi8->fmadd, hsum,
  scalar tail) under #if __AVX2__&&__FMA__; scalar fallback = null floor. Wired into BOTH
  matmul_arena row paths (Q4B per-32-block, Q8/Q4 whole-row).
- sp_arena_row_dot (exported, sp/forward_dispatch.h): single-row packed dot — unpack-if-Q4
  into caller scratch + SIMD dot + row/block scales. expert_mm's arena path now uses it,
  SKIPPING the f32 dequant-row write entirely (sp_frob_packed_dequant_row no longer on the
  MoE hot path). Header gotcha receipted: sp_frob_packed_tensor is an anonymous-struct
  typedef — a `struct` fwd-decl does NOT match; include frobenius_lift.h.
- Perf build flags: -DCMAKE_C_FLAGS="/openmp /arch:AVX2" (default builds carry neither =
  serial scalar null floor, byte-identical).

PRE-REGISTERED GATE (SIMD changes accumulation order => top-1/sequence, NOT bit-parity):
  35B OK-container, real-vocab prompt, greedy 16, QWEN36_STEP=1:
  SEQ = 760 6511 314 9338 369 11751 13 198 32 13 2912 198 33 13 3439 271 248068 271 8160 579 264
  — IDENTICAL 21/21 to the scalar/serial/stateless sequences anyway (every near-tie held).
