  CUMULATIVE                                       **89x**   (~0.6s/token flat)

RE-PROFILE (SP_Q36_PROF, ~0.65s/step): moe 43% | gdn_mm 28% | head 14% | conv+recur 8% |
attn 8%. SIMD gain modest (1.41x) because the step is now dominated by DISPATCH overhead,
not ALU: the MoE runs 8 experts x 3 matmuls x 40 layers = ~960 OpenMP fork-joins/token over
SMALL row counts (FF=512). BRICK 6 (pre-scoped): (a) hoist the parallel region — one
omp-parallel per moe_ffn (or per step) with omp-for over a flattened (expert x row) space;
(b) batch gate+up per expert (same rows, two outputs) to halve row passes; (c) then the GPU
residency ladder. The conv+recurrence (8%) is still scalar-serial — thread per-head if it
ever tops the profile.
